<p>DISCLAIMER: This is not a project done for a company. Making coffee is a part of my, and many of my friends', morning routine. I'm always looking for easy ways to up my coffee game, so I thought I'd design a mobile app to do just that. Apart from being an app I'd actually use, designing it also let me focus on developing my prototyping skills using the Sketch App.</p>

<section id="challenge">
<h2>The Challenge</h2>
<p><u>Background</u>: There are many components to making a high-quality pour over coffee. If youâ€™re not a barista, it can be tricky to improve how well you brew. </p>

<p><u>Goal</u>: Create a mobile app that lets you track important metrics about pour overs you make, assign a rating to each cup, and provides feedback/suggestions for improving tour skill. </p>

<p><u>My Role</u>: Interaction designer and user researcher.</p> 
</section>


