<h4>Wireframes and Prototypes</h4>

<h4>Apple Watch Prototypes</h4>
<p>The main feature of this thing is the stopwatch. A minimal Apple watch app lets users record their brew using their watch. They can also rate their brew, and later on add notes from their phone (or use Siri to dictate them). </p>
</section>




<section id="results">
<h2>Results</h2>
<p>As I mentioned at the top, this was a fictional project. My aim was to design an app to solve a problem that I (and my friends) have when it comes to making pour-over coffee: how do we get better making only one or two cups a day, and without any mentoring? This app makes it simple and easy torecord important metrics for brewing coffee. With some built in reminders about what you liked and what you didn't (and maybe a little help from some AI), everyone can brew better coffee.</p>

<p>P.S. Interested in actually developing this app? I'm more than willing to talk about how to turn this into a reality. Please see my <a href=/contact>contact page</a> to get in touch.</p>
</section>
